Cookie Cartel

by: Asher Feren

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I wanted to make a game that made me laugh while coding. I wanted to take things that should never be in a sentence together and put them together. Cookies, grandmas, and cartels. Unfortunately, I made it funny, but not so entertaining.

2. What I Learned

Due to Covid restrictions, I made my game while on zoom. This made me unable to use my peers for critique.

3. Architecture of My Game

I made a class for just about anything you could imagine. A class for the cookie, a class for the images, a class that combines the other classes, and a class that runs the game.

4. Technical Implementation

I'm not proud of a specific part of my game necessarily. I am most proud that I was able to design and create a completely original game with no instructions while on zoom.

5. Most Challenging Part

As I said, there were no instructions guiding me through the process of creating the first game I've designed and coded. Creating my game while on zoom made things more difficult as well.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I had bigger aspirations for my game. I didn't realize how hard it is to make the most simple function work. I had to eliminate lots of ideas as I coded, leaving my game stripped of everything that might have been entertaining; except for the grandmas of course!
